      <div type="notes" xml:lang="en">
	<p>This edition and translation is based on <ref target="bibl:Chandra1919">Chandra 1919–1920</ref>.</p>
      </div>
      <div type="edition" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
	<p>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	    <gap reason="lost"
		 quantity="3"
		 unit="character"
		 precision="low"/>gāme vāthavasa gahapatisa <persName
		 key="pers:Am-Vākāṭaka">vākāṭakasa</persName> 
	    gahapatiki<unclear>ni</unclear>
	  <lb n="2"/>
	    <gap reason="lost"
		 quantity="5"
		 unit="character"
		 precision="low"/>nā therena <persName 
		 key="pers:Am-Bodhika">bodhikena</persName> bhariyāya
	    <persName key="pers:Am-Camunā">camunāya</persName> sabhātukehi<gap
	         reason="lost"
		 quantity="3"
		 unit="character"
		 precision="low"/>
	  <lb n="3"/>
	    <gap reason="lost"
		 quantity="3"
		 unit="character"
		 precision="low"/>kehi sanātimitabaṃdhavehi ca
	    apaṇo āyuvadhanika<unclear>pu</unclear><gap
	         reason="lost"
		 quantity="4"
		 unit="character"
		 precision="low"/>
	</p>
      </div>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
	<p>Of the householder <persName key="pers:Am-Vākāṭaka">Vākāṭaka</persName>,
	an inhabitant of the village... of the housewife ... by the thera
	<persName key="pers:Am-Bodhika">Bodhika</persName>... of his wife
	<persName key="pers:Am-Camunā">Camunā</persName> with her brothers...
	with grandsons, friends, and relatives also, for the increment
	of his own term of life...</p>
      </div>
